'''Morality''' (from Latin ''{{lang|la|moralitas}}'' "manner, character, proper behaviour") refers to the concept of human action which pertains to matters of right and wrong — also referred to as "[[good and evil]]" — used within three contexts: individual [[conscience]]; systems of [[principle]]s and [[judgment]]s — sometimes called [[moral value]]s —shared within a [[cultural]], [[religion|religious]], [[secular]] or [[philosophical]] community; and codes of behavior or [[Code of conduct|conduct morality]].
